      "acceptanceCriteria": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary QoI and is directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is defined as the ratio of device hemolysis to predicate device hemolysis under matched flow conditions. This quantity maps directly to the FDA acceptance criterion (RH < 1) and is the sole basis for the regulatory decision. QoI relevance is fully established."
    },
